com.b2international.snowowl.core.api

Interface IComponentIconIdProvider<K>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - - type of the unique component identifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FixedIconIdProvider, SnomedConceptIconIdProvider, SnomedDescriptionIconIdProvider, SnomedRefSetIconIdProvider, SnomedRelationshipIconIdProvider

    public interface IComponentIconIdProvider<K>
    Provides terminology specific component IDs for resolving icons on the UI.

    • Method Detail

      • getIconId

        @Nullable
K getIconId(IBranchPoint branchPoint,
                       K componentId)
        Returns with the ID of a component who's icon should be revealed for a particular component given by it terminology wise unique component identifier.

        May return with null e.g.: the component does not exist at the branch in the given time.

        Parameters:
        branchPoint - the branch point uniquely identifying a branch and a point in time.
        componentId - the unique identifier of the component.
        Returns:
        the unique ID of a component who's icon should be associated with the current component.

      • getIconId

        @Nullable
K getIconId(IBranchPath branchPath,
                       K componentId)
        Returns with the ID of the component whos's icon is associated with the given terminology independent component.

        NOTE: this method only searches for icon IDs only the most recent state of the given branch. If client has to lookup icon IDs for historical revisions of a particular component, then clients should use getIconId(IBranchPoint, Object) instead.

        Parameters:
        branchPath - the branch path for the operation.
        componentId - the unique component ID.
        Returns:
        the unique ID of a component who's icon should be associated with the current component.
